msgctxt "an10.113:0.1"
msgid "Aṅguttara Nikāya 10 "
msgstr "Numbered Discourses 10 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "an10.113:0.2"
msgid "12. Paccorohaṇivagga "
msgstr "12. The Ceremony of Descent "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "an10.113:0.3"
msgid "113. Paṭhamaadhammasutta "
msgstr "113. Bad Principles (1st) "

# NOTE: Here and following BB’s translation is less than ideal. Dhamma is not translated, and attha/anattha is, I think, mistranslated. Here it is clearly the result of the dhamma. The point is not that it is “beneficial”, i.e. that is creates benefit, but that it is a benefit created by the dhamma. Dhamma is cause, attha effect.
#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: sc1
msgctxt "an10.113:1.1"
msgid "“Adhammo ca, bhikkhave, veditabbo anattho ca; "
msgstr "“Mendicants, you should know bad principles with bad results. "

msgctxt "an10.113:1.2"
msgid "dhammo ca veditabbo attho ca. "
msgstr "And you should know good principles with good results. "

msgctxt "an10.113:1.3"
msgid "Adhammañca viditvā anatthañca, dhammañca viditvā atthañca yathā dhammo yathā attho tathā paṭipajjitabbaṃ. "
msgstr "Knowing these things, your practice should follow the good principles with good results. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts-vp-pli5.223, sc2
msgctxt "an10.113:2.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, adhammo ca anattho ca? "
msgstr "And what are bad principles with bad results? "

msgctxt "an10.113:2.2"
msgid "Micchādiṭṭhi, micchāsaṅkappo, micchāvācā, micchākammanto, micchāājīvo, micchāvāyāmo, micchāsati, micchāsamādhi, micchāñāṇaṃ, micchāvimutti—"
msgstr "Wrong view, wrong thought, wrong speech, wrong action, wrong livelihood, wrong effort, wrong mindfulness, wrong immersion, wrong knowledge, and wrong freedom. "

msgctxt "an10.113:2.3"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, adhammo ca anattho ca. "
msgstr "These are called bad principles with bad results. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc3
msgctxt "an10.113:3.1"
msgid "Katamo ca, bhikkhave, dhammo ca attho ca? "
msgstr "And what are good principles with good results? "

msgctxt "an10.113:3.2"
msgid "Sammādiṭṭhi, sammāsaṅkappo, sammāvācā, sammākammanto, sammāājīvo, sammāvāyāmo, sammāsati, sammāsamādhi, sammāñāṇaṃ, sammāvimutti—"
msgstr "Right view, right thought, right speech, right action, right livelihood, right effort, right mindfulness, right immersion, right knowledge, and right freedom. "

msgctxt "an10.113:3.3"
msgid "ayaṃ vuccati, bhikkhave, dhammo ca attho ca. "
msgstr "These are called good principles with good results. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "an10.113:4.1"
msgid "‘Adhammo ca, bhikkhave, veditabbo anattho ca; "
msgstr "‘You should know bad principles with bad results. "

msgctxt "an10.113:4.2"
msgid "dhammo ca veditabbo attho ca. "
msgstr "And you should know good principles with good results. "

msgctxt "an10.113:4.3"
msgid "Adhammañca viditvā anatthañca, dhammañca viditvā atthañca yathā dhammo yathā attho tathā paṭipajjitabban’ti, "
msgstr "Knowing these things, your practice should follow the good principles with good results.’ "

msgctxt "an10.113:4.4"
msgid "iti yaṃ taṃ vuttaṃ, idametaṃ paṭicca vuttan”ti. "
msgstr "That’s what I said, and this is why I said it.” "

#. HTML: </p><p class="endsection">
msgctxt "an10.113:4.5"
msgid "Paṭhamaṃ. "
msgstr ""

